They differ by their vowel sounds:

11
00:00:50,220 --> 00:00:52,740
the /ɑ/ in "spa"

12
00:00:52,740 --> 00:00:55,500
and the /aɪ/ in "spy."

13
00:00:56,100 --> 00:01:00,520
Now, watch and compare what happens when you pronounce these vowels:

14
00:01:07,180 --> 00:01:11,100
Do you see the difference in how your tongue and jaw move?

15
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:13,820
When you pronounce the /ɑ/ sound,

16
00:01:13,820 --> 00:01:17,720
your tongue and jaw move into one position only.

17
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:20,880
When you pronounce the /aɪ/ vowel,

18
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:23,920
they move from one position to another.

19
00:01:26,580 --> 00:01:30,040
The /ɑ/ is what is called a "monophthong,"

20
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,620
which means "a single sound."

21
00:01:32,620 --> 00:01:35,480
So, you pronounce only one sound.

22
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:39,180
The /aɪ/, however, is a "diphthong."

23
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:44,020
It means that it's made by merging two single sounds into one.

24
00:01:48,460 --> 00:01:51,620
That's why your jaw and tongue change their positions

25
00:01:51,620 --> 00:01:53,320
as you make the first sound

26
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:55,540
and then connect it to the second.

27
00:01:58,900 --> 00:02:02,320
There are three diphthongs in American English,

28
00:02:02,340 --> 00:02:07,280
the /aɪ/, the /ɔɪ/ and the /aʊ/,

29
00:02:07,960 --> 00:02:14,500
as in the words "by," "boy," and "bow."

30
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:20,360
We'll cover the /ɔɪ/ and the /aʊ/ in our future videos.

31
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:24,420
As for the /aɪ/, let's find out how to pronounce this sound.

32
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:28,500
To make the /aɪ/ diphthong correctly,

33
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:32,800
you need to pronounce two sounds and make a smooth connection between them.

34
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:35,780
This is how you do that.

35
00:02:35,940 --> 00:02:38,860
Start with making the /ɑ/ sound.

36
00:02:39,540 --> 00:02:41,900
Open your mouth as wide as possible.

37
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:48,260
Relax your lips and allow them to rest in a neutral position.

38
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:54,260
Flatten your tongue

39
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:58,020
and place it very low in your mouth.

40
00:03:00,820 --> 00:03:04,980
The tip of your tongue should be touching the back of your bottom front teeth.

41
00:03:07,580 --> 00:03:13,300
Next, connect the /ɑ/ to the /ɪ/ sound.

42
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:15,480
Smoothly move your jaw up,

43
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:20,960
until your mouth is almost closed and push your tongue forward,

44
00:03:21,020 --> 00:03:24,000
raising it high in your mouth.

45
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:31,540
The first sound in a diphthong is typically longer and louder.

46
00:03:31,620 --> 00:03:36,540
So, make sure that you pronounce a nice and full /ɑ/

47
00:03:36,540 --> 00:03:39,100
and then connect it to the /ɪ/.

48
