Now, let's glide from the /ɑ/ to the /ɪ/ and blend the two sounds together:

49
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:58,320
When you pronounce words with the /aɪ/ sound,

50
00:03:58,320 --> 00:04:01,360
try to avoid the most common pronunciation mistake.

51
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:09,360
Many non-native speakers reduce the /ɪ/ sound in the /aɪ/.

52
00:04:09,540 --> 00:04:12,580
As a result, the whole sound gets distorted,

53
00:04:12,580 --> 00:04:14,760
and it may lead to misunderstandings.

54
